description.narrative: The importance of multi-lingual education was advocated to the parliamentarians of Chin State to become advocates themselves for decisions to fulfill the rights of ethnic children. Programme adaptations are in progress to continue with new normal approaches as most system strengthening efforts were constrained by COVID-19 pandemic in Myanmar. The guidelines for pre-school reopening developed by EAPRO was adapted into Myanmar language to be distributed. Established South-South and Triangular Cooperation with Ministry of Commerce of People's Republic of China, with support from China National Committee, and secured 800,000 USD to support COVID related interventions for new normalcy. | Status:Constrained | As-of Date:21/07/2020
